summary: My feminist brain: the captain marvel movie is being used as military propaganda and attempting to manipulate young girls into...
body:
My feminist brain: the captain marvel movie is being used as military propaganda and attempting to manipulate young girls into believing they are empowering themselves by becoming another cog in the US’s military industrial complex that hurts POC and women both domestically and internationally as well as the movie controlled by the Air Force in order to paint it as a sympathetic evil fighting force is propaganda and we should view it as a first step in America’s growing development into fascism. As well as this being marvels first attempt at making a “female” super hero movie this late in the game is shameful and is only them attempting to capitalize off of and weaponnzie femininityespecially after they claimed it would not succeed until DC proved otherwise with Wonder Woman’s success (Wonder Woman also has its faults but thats a discussion for a different day) and it should be virewed as cowardly and a cash grab not as something marvel actually wanted to do. The very fact that this so called feminist movie is encouraging girls to hurt become part of a system that is used an oppressive force throughout the second and third world is terrifying and should not be seen as empowering.

Sapphic brain: Brie Larsen,,,,,,,, segggsy

summary: Can I have a Yon-Rogg reader x with this prompt: "You are adorable, you think you can beat me."
question: Can I have a Yon-Rogg reader x with this prompt: "You are adorable, you think you can beat me."
answer:
I mean I’ve never seen a prompt more suited to him 😂 - A x

— x —

In Training - Reader x Yon-Rogg

Rating: General Audiences

Pairing: Reader x Yon-Rogg

Warnings: None

Abbrevaitations: None

Requester: See Above

Request: See Above

— x —

• Masterlist • Prompts • Commission •

— x —

Panting, back to the mat, chest aching with how hard your lungs and heart were working, and with your legs unwilling to move to help you stand again, you groaned in pain.

“Come on,” Your partner teased from halfway down the mat. “You can do better than that, can’t you?”

Rolling over onto your stomach and then finally standing again, you turned to face him, eyes all steely determination as they locked with his bright amber ones. You would never admit it but your kneecaps felt like they were knocking your tibias with how shaky they were.

“How long have we been going?” You asked him, feeling great annoyance at his smug smirk.

“Not long enough.” He told you firmly.

“I disagree.” You raised your arms, ready to go again. “We’ve been going far too long. If I beat you this next time, we’re done and I’m getting something to eat.”

“You’re adorable if you think you can beat me.” He looked at you as if he took pity on you, and that turned your annoyance into rage. It was a common tactic he used; you knew this. But it got you every time.

Rushing him, you weren’t surprised when you quickly ended up back down on the mat again.

“Control your emotions.” It was the same mantra he always gave you; the same tagline he’d used with all those he trained.

“I can’t when you’re being such an asshole.” You refused stubbornly to move. You were damn fine right where you were, thank you very much.

“You would if you remained calm.” He kept on at you with that emotionless robot line. Sometimes you thought he was one.

Yon-Rogg’s hand appeared in front of your face and you took it, letting him haul you to your feet.

“Look,” He looked at you with more care than you had seen from him previously and you felt your heart beat faster still, though this time for a different reason. “I only push you because I love you and I wouldn’t be able to see you lost to battle.”

“I know.” You smiled, tiptoeing to kiss his cheek in thanks for his rare emotional honesty. “I love you too.”

Walking to face him, sparring distance apart once more, you pulled up your fists and smiled. Still panting, still with your muscles burning, knowing you were going to regret this, you determinedly nodded.

“Let’s go again.”
